   1.   Install [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/stardewvalley/mods/1720]Json Assets[/url]﻿ to get all the hats and clothes in,

   ﻿2.   ﻿If you're updating [b]from before 4.2[/b], you'll need to [b]delete all the old Sailor Styles stuff[/b],

   ﻿3.   Download this mod, and ﻿drop the [b]Sailor Styles[/b] folder into your [b]Mods[/b] folder.

   ﻿+   Not using hairstyles? Disable them in the config file!
   ﻿+   Want skirts for your shirts? Get the custom pants from [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/stardewvalley/mods/6143]Kisekae Skirts[/url]!
   ﻿+   Add more content packs to Artemis' shop in the config, just add their unique ID!

The world's a slightly better place for having a whole bunch of silly shirts going international. If you're keen on writing little translations for 100+ shirts and items, get into contact with me via Nexus messages! Currently we've only got the two languages above sorted, so feel free to get involved!

I try to keep on top of my inbox, but bless Eros for sending me a full translation in April and having me release it in August. Blueberry time is wild.
Translations are encouraged to be bundled with the mod to make updates easier for you and me. If I'm not contactable, you can post your translation on the Nexus.

With the spirit of the solar and lunar new years around us, what better way to celebrate than going out in a fresh change of clothes? The 4.0 update brings out the old to ring in the new year! Artemis' shop at the Hat Mouse House sells colourful kimono all year round as long as he's in town, so you can liven up your farm with some beautiful seasonal robes.

These kimono are styled after the 25th anniversary release Sakura Kimono Festival chibifigs, with some brand new designs for the outers, as well as a dyeable plain variety. Show your colours!


[img]https://i.imgur.com/1uMqkhY.png[/img]
You'll find Artemis selling a selection of clothes [b]every Sunday and Monday[/b], all day long, for a small price each. He'll be waiting beside the Hat Mouse, whether you're playing with the vanilla game or with Stardew Valley Expanded.
Those bows might not exactly fit a lot of hairstyles, by the way - that's just how they work - but they should fit most!

All the clothing additions currently available are:
[size=4]
   ﻿・School uniforms,﻿
   ﻿・Sailor suits,
   ﻿・Shrine robes,
   ﻿・[b]11 different colours of kimono[/b],
   ﻿・and about [b]100 more new custom outfits![/b]
[/size]
All the new clothing options are directly based on the fashion of the show, and made to match the style of Stardew Valley while holding onto their ridiculous, gaudy, and vibrant charm and style. See if there's any you know and love!


[img]https://i.imgur.com/gRVWwvh.png[/img]

This pack adds in a range of new hairstyles from all the inner and outer sailors, with both their original colours as well as a customisable colour base available to use. You can choose these in the character creator or from the Wizard's magic mirror.
If you're playing with [b]Customize Anywhere[/b], you can use that, too: its default hotkey is [b]Shift+2[/b].
All hairstyles are fully recolourable with their own custom gradient maps, so you can give your favourite styles a lime-green dye job!
Don't want to have the new hairstyles in your character creator? You can disable extra styles in [size=4][font=Courier New]config.json[/font][/size] .
